The government will be strict and vigilant with the marking of national exams, Education CS Fred Matiang&rsquo;i said yesterday.He spoke in Wamagana, Tetu subcounty, where he witnessed the collection of of KCSE exam papers by secondary school principals at 6am.&ldquo;We shall not drop our eyes from the ball. We will manage the marking of examinations with military precision,&rdquo; Matiang&rsquo;i said.He also witnessed the collection exam papers from Nyeri Central subcounty headquarters in Nyeri town. Matiang&rsquo;i was joined by PS Belio Kipsang. He thanked principals and teachers&rsquo; union officials for their support in ensuring credibility of exams.&ldquo;We don&rsquo;t want to teach our children fraud by giving them results obtained irregularly and through malpractices,&rdquo; Matiang&rsquo;i affirmed. He said candidates&rsquo; results will be true and genuine.